A port to Ruby of Perl's Data::RandomPerson.

http://search.cpan.org/~peterhi/Data-RandomPerson-0.4/

Initially just the Names portion.


Usage:

For example, to generate 1000 random people with Spanish names, between the ages of 16 and 35 with a ratio of 3 males to every 5 females:

Load all the files (once this is a gem this can be ignored):
irb -r Generator.rb -r Choice.rb -r Person.rb -r extensions/Date.rb -r extensions/Array.rb -r extensions/Enumerable.rb -r extensions/Kernel.rb -r extensions/Set.rb -r extensions/Hash.rb --noinspect

choice = RandomPerson::Choice.new( {gender_ratio: [3,5] , age_lower:16, age_upper:35 } )

choice.add_Spanish

g = RandomPerson::Generator.new

g.make_generator choice

people = [ ]

1000.times { people << g.generators[0].call }

10.times { |i| puts "#{people[i].first} #{people[i].last} age: #{people[i].age} born: #{people[i].dob.strftime("%d-%b-%Y")}" }

